# @VERSION spec:gdls v:0.1.0 generated:2026-03-22 source:schema-agent
# @FORMAT COLUMN|SQL_TYPE|NULLABLE|KEY|DESCRIPTION
# Project Atlas — target ledger schema (to-be)

@D atlas_finance|Atlas modernised ledger schema (Postgres 16) — produced by tech-design phase

@T GeneralLedger|Account master — modernised, with explicit currency and lifecycle handling
account_id|UUID|N|PK|Primary key
account_code|VARCHAR(40)|N||Chart of accounts code (unique)
account_name|VARCHAR(200)|N||Display name
status|VARCHAR(20)|N||Lifecycle status
parent_id|UUID|Y|FK|Parent account
currency_iso|CHAR(3)|N||ISO 4217 code
opened_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||When the account was opened
closed_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|Y||If closed, when
created_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Row creation timestamp
updated_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Last mutation timestamp
@E GeneralLedger.status|ACTIVE,INACTIVE,CLOSED,FROZEN|Account lifecycle status

@T JournalEntry|Journal entries — versioned and immutably linked to source events
entry_id|UUID|N|PK|Primary key
posting_date|DATE|N||Effective accounting date
account_id|UUID|N|FK|Account reference
amount|NUMERIC(28,8)|N||Posted amount in account currency
amount_base|NUMERIC(28,8)|Y||Base-currency translation snapshot
fx_rate|NUMERIC(18,8)|Y||FX rate snapshot
source_kind|VARCHAR(30)|N||Origin classification
source_event_id|UUID|Y||Upstream event identifier (Kafka offset)
posted_by|VARCHAR(120)|N||Service or user identity
posted_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Wall-clock when posted
reverses_entry_id|UUID|Y|FK|Reversed entry, if applicable
batch_id|UUID|Y|FK|Batch identifier
version|INTEGER|N||Increments on supersession
@E JournalEntry.source_kind|MANUAL,PAYMENT,CDC,FX_REVAL,RECON_ADJUSTMENT,IMPORT|Provenance of the entry

@T PaymentBatch|Payment batches — preserved for traceability even though entries arrive via Kafka
batch_id|UUID|N|PK|Primary key
upstream_topic|VARCHAR(120)|N||Kafka topic that fed the batch
window_start|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Earliest event in the batch
window_end|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Latest event in the batch
entry_count|INTEGER|N||Entries posted from batch
status|VARCHAR(20)|N||Processing state
@E PaymentBatch.status|RECEIVED,PROCESSED,RECONCILED,FAILED

@T Customer|Customer master — sourced from Salesforce CDC
customer_id|UUID|N|PK|Internal identifier
sf_external_id|VARCHAR(64)|N||Salesforce ID (unique)
display_name|VARCHAR(200)|N||Display name
tier|VARCHAR(20)|Y||Customer tier
region|VARCHAR(40)|Y||Operational region
synced_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Last CDC sync
@E Customer.tier|STRATEGIC,ENTERPRISE,MID,SMB

@T ReconciliationRun|Per-period reconciliation run — strict, gating month-end close
run_id|UUID|N|PK|Primary key
period|VARCHAR(7)|N||YYYY-MM
started_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Start
completed_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|Y||Completion
status|VARCHAR(20)|N||Outcome
variance_total|NUMERIC(28,8)|Y||Variance summed across runs
gate_passed|BOOLEAN|Y||Whether close was allowed to proceed
@E ReconciliationRun.status|RUNNING,SUCCESS,VARIANCE,FAILED

@T AuditEvent|Append-only audit events mirrored from Kafka
audit_id|UUID|N|PK|Primary key
event_ts|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Event timestamp
actor|VARCHAR(120)|N||Acting principal (mandatory now)
entity|VARCHAR(40)|N||Entity affected
entity_id|UUID|N||Entity identifier
operation|VARCHAR(20)|N||Operation
prior_version|INTEGER|Y||Previous version
new_version|INTEGER|Y||Resulting version
@E AuditEvent.operation|INSERT,UPDATE,SUPERSEDE,REVERSE,CLOSE,GATE

@R JournalEntry.account_id -> GeneralLedger.account_id|fk|Journal entry to account
@R JournalEntry.reverses_entry_id -> JournalEntry.entry_id|fk|Reversal linkage
@R JournalEntry.batch_id -> PaymentBatch.batch_id|fk|Batch traceability
@R GeneralLedger.parent_id -> GeneralLedger.account_id|fk|Account hierarchy
@R AuditEvent.entity_id -> JournalEntry.entry_id|polymorphic|Audit reference (polymorphic)
@R PaymentBatch.batch_id -> ReconciliationRun.run_id|reconciles|Batch reconciliation
